                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety Airways/83:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-29T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 29, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>363. Reference Department’s 227, July 11 [<hi rend="italic">10</hi>], 6 p.m.
                    Authorization granted. Governors being informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
